    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-28T19:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-28T19:45:00-05:00" n="614"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Brazil/1355a Supplement:
                    Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-28T20:45:00-04:00"
                            >January 28, 1943—8:45 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–831. Department’s 2721, September 15, 1942, 10 p.m.<note n="25"
                        xml:id="d614fn25">
                        <ref target="frus1942v05#pg_717">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 717</ref>.</note> What progress is
                    being made to curtail production of non-essential rubber products through a
                    system of government control?</p>
                <p>Korkegi’s recent memorandum to Cooke,<note n="26" xml:id="d614fn26">Memorandum
                        not found in Department files; Mr. Korkegi and Mr. Cooke were officials of
                        the Rubber Reserve Company.</note> Rubber Reserve, poses the question of
                    whether immediate limitation can best be accomplished by a Rubber Reserve
                    program of purchasing or governmental decree or both. What appears to be the
                    chance of any action in the near future on part of Brazilian Government?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
